The paper discusses a technique for improving tail latencies in distributed systems, specifically in-memory key-value stores. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on data structures and algorithms for key-value stores, which could place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper also discusses load balancing and hardware dispatching, which could place it in the Operating Systems (cs.OS) sub-category. The paper could also belong to the Architecture (cs.AR) sub-category, as it discusses the implementation of a specific key-value store. Finally, the paper discusses performance metrics and optimization, which could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
